The paper deals with the problem of online load balancing, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for online linear optimization, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper uses probabilistic analysis and smoothing techniques, which are common in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses worst-case and random-order models, which are common in game theory (cs.GT) and online learning (cs.NE).
